cs.NE, cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NI

The paper discusses a computational model inspired by the ventral visual pathway in the brain, which is related to neural networks and machine learning (cs.NE). The model is designed for object recognition in natural images, which falls under computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also discusses the use of learning rules and the evaluation of the model's performance, which are related to machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper uses statistical analysis techniques to show the effectiveness of the model, which is related to neural information processing (cs.NI).
